# OpenSpec default workflow

This project uses **OpenSpec v1.5** (`openspec/`). Treat OPSX as the default way to plan and ship work — not an optional add-on.

## When to use OpenSpec

| User intent | Default action |
|-------------|----------------|
| New feature, refactor, or non-trivial fix | OpenSpec change required before coding |
| Requirements unclear | Read & follow `.cursor/skills/openspec-explore/SKILL.md` |
| Scope is clear | Read & follow `.cursor/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md` |
| Implementing an active change | Read & follow `.cursor/skills/openspec-apply-change/SKILL.md` |
| Change done, merge specs | Read & follow `.cursor/skills/openspec-sync-specs/SKILL.md` |
| Close out a change | Read & follow `.cursor/skills/openspec-archive-change/SKILL.md` |

## Default flow (core profile)

```text
/opsx:explore (optional) → /opsx:propose → /opsx:apply → /opsx:sync → /opsx:archive
```

Even when the user does not type slash commands, **follow the same phases** using the matching skill above.

## Before writing code

1. Run `openspec list --json` — if an active change exists, continue it; do not start a parallel change unless the user asks.
2. If no change exists and the request is more than a one-line fix or pure Q&A, create one via `openspec new change "<kebab-name>"` and generate artifacts (propose path) before editing source.
3. During apply, use `openspec status --change "<name>" --json` and `openspec instructions apply --change "<name>" --json` to drive task order.

## Exceptions (skip OpenSpec)

- Pure questions, code review, or explanation with no implementation
- Trivial edits explicitly scoped by the user (typo, comment, config one-liner)
- User explicitly says "skip openspec" or "just do it"

When skipping, say briefly why OpenSpec was bypassed.

## Conventions

- Change names: kebab-case, intent-clear (`add-user-auth`, not `feature-1`)
- Specs live under `openspec/specs/`; active work under `openspec/changes/`
- Respect `openspec/config.yaml` context and artifact rules when generating artifacts
- Brownfield-first: write delta specs only for what you change, not the whole codebase
